===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|敎|𦥑|宀|t1=to teach|t2=mingling hands; hands-on learning|t3=house; roofed building|abb1=yes|ls=ic}} – a child learns in a roofed place. See {{zh-l|敎/教}} for more.

In the modern form, 宀 has corrupted to {{zh-l|*冖|[[cover]]}}, and the hands 𦥑 around the {{zh-l|*爻}} have become connected with the roof 冖 on top of the child {{zh-l|*子}}. Ancient forms include {{zh-l|*斆}} and {{zh-l|*斅}}, which preserve more of {{zh-l|*敎}}. ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' regards {{zh-l|*𦥑}} as the phonetic component in the character, which may be true according to some Old Chinese reconstructions such as that of {{w|Pan Wuyun}}'s, though probably not others.

The earliest oracle bone script forms may be a {{Han compound|爻|六|c1=s|c2=p|ls=psc|nocap=y}}.

